main event: An RB-26 aircraft observed a bright orange glow traveling at least 600 mph on a 120 degree heading at 7000 ft.
interesting points: The glow appeared to be coming from an object smaller than that of a jet aircraft exhaust.
The glow did not diminish but went out suddenly.
The navigator stated that the glow bore great similarity to a World War II V-1 rocket.
The sighting occurred on 012110-I Jan 52 at BS6070 in Korea.
The document is classified as UNCLASSIFIED and is subject to declassification after 12 years.
